service: queue
slug: queue
kind: Queue
archetype: generated-service-manager
status/finalizer: required /
retain-until-confirmed-delete
requeue: provisioning, updating, terminating
provider states: create CREATING, UPDATING;
update UPDATING; delete DELETING
supported drift: channel_consumption_limit,
custom_encryption_key_id,
dead_letter_queue_delivery_count, defined_tags
(+4 more)
reject before mutate: force-new fields
compartment_id, retention_in_seconds
create-only fields: none
list lookup: oci_queue_queues filters
compartment_id, display_name, id,
lifecycle_state
conflicts: none
open gaps: none
Queue create, update, and delete are
work-request-backed. The runtime persists
createWorkRequestId, updateWorkRequestId, and
deleteWorkRequestId in status so reconcile
resumes asynchronous OCI operations across
requeues instead of relying on name-only lookup.
Create binds identity from Queue work-request
resources, then reads the Queue by recovered
OCID before projecting status. Delete is not
best-effort; it only completes after GetQueue
confirms the tracked Queue is gone or exposes
lifecycle state DELETED.
Mutable drift is limited to UpdateQueueDetails
fields such as displayName, timeout, visibility,
tags, channelConsumptionLimit,
deadLetterQueueDeliveryCount, and
customEncryptionKeyId. Create-only inputs like
compartmentId and retentionInSeconds are
rejected as force-new drift.
A package-local companion writes or updates the
same-name endpoint Secret only after ACTIVE when
messagesEndpoint is present, adopts only
unlabeled matching Secrets, uses guarded
updates/deletes for owned Secrets, and skips
missing or unowned Secrets during delete
cleanup.
end note
note right of delete_pending
delete policy: required
delete observe: GetQueue or ListQueues
delete targets: DELETED
Secret cleanup waits for OCI delete
confirmation.
end note
